<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="about.action"><B>about.action</B></a>
<DD>September 1994 brief description of the ACTION mailing list
    including background, rationale, and objectives.
<DT><a href="action.charter"><B>action.charter</B></a>
<DD>Stanton McCandlish's September 1994 document introducing
    the ACTION mailing list which networks online activists.
<DT><a href="action.faq"><B>action.faq</B></a>
<DD>Stanton McCandlish's September 1994 FAQ regarding the
    Activism Online Mailing List "ACTION".
<DT><a href="activ_groups.faq"><B>activ_groups.faq</B></a>
<DD>September 1994 FAQ/list of "Outposts on the Electronic
    Frontier" including information about International, National, Regional
    & Local Groups Supporting the Online Community 
<DT><a href="activ_resource.faq"><B>activ_resource.faq</B></a>
<DD>A September 1994 list of Usenet newsgroups, Internet
    mailing lists and other resources of use to the online activist.
<DT><a href="congress_email.faq"><B>congress_email.faq</B></a>
<DD>September 1994 list of congressional e-mail addresses 
<DT><a href="govt_contact.list"><B>govt_contact.list</B></a>
<DD>September 1994 list of US government contact
    information, including phone, fax, postal address and email address for
    Congresspersons and White House staff 
<DT><a href="project.list"><B>project.list</B></a>
<DD>list of projects the EFF will be or is undertaking
</DL>

