<H2><A NAME="dirs">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/filefolder_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40
ALT=""></A> Subdirectories in This Archive</H2>

<DL>
<DT><A HREF=".."><B>Up to the Parent Directory</B><P></a>
<DT><a href="Clipper_II/"><B>Clipper_II/</B></A>
<DD>Link to directory of info on later (1995) NIST &quot;Clipper II&quot;
    key &quot;escrow&quot; scheme
<DT><a href="Clipper_III/"><B>Clipper_III/</B></A>
<DD>Link to directory of info on later (1996) IWGCP &quot;Clipper III&quot;
    key &quot;escrow&quot; scheme
<DT><a href="Clipper_FOIA/"><B>Clipper_FOIA/</B></A>
<DD>Link to a directory pertaining to EFF board member John 
    Gilmore's attempt at filing a Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) 
    request with the Clipper key 'escrow agents' for the database of 
    Clipper key components.
<DT><a href="Euro-Clipper/"><B>Euro-Clipper/</B></A>
<DD>directory of info on key &quot;escrow&quot; and &quot;trusted third party&quot;
    schemes in Europe, labelled &quot;Euro-Clipper&quot; by many.
<DT><a href="Key_escrow/"><B>Key_escrow/</B></A>
<DD>link to directory of files on the US Administration's
    1995 (and onward? We hope not...) &quot;Clipper 2&quot;: Commercial key escrow.
    This issue ties in directly with ITAR crypto export policy (see 
    /pub/Privacy/ITAR_export/).
<DT><a href="Old/"><B>Old/</B></A>
<DD>Old/outdated material, preserved for historical interest.
</DL>

