Atlas</A> server</B>
<DD>loads of telecom information.
<DT><B>Pacific Systems Group's <A
HREF="gopher://rain.psg.com/11/networks/connect/">Global
    Connectivity</A> Gopher Archive</B>
<DD>a large amount of info by world region on
    state of connectivity, where to find net access, etc.  Impressive.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.nla.gov.au/lis/govnii.html">Government Policy
&amp; the Information Superhighway</A></B>
<DD>(from the National Library of Australia. Focusses on Aus. govt.
policy, but also features several other countries.
<DT><A HREF="http://communication.sbs.ohio-state.edu/cast/">Center for 
Advanced Study in Telecommunications</A></B>
<DD>CAST exists "to provide a clearing
   house for researchers, government agencies and telecommunications
   businesses and...to act as a "level playing field" for discussion of
   controversial issues of public importance in telecommunications policy
   and application."
</DL>

