<H2><A NAME="dirs">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/filefolder_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40
ALT=""></A> Subdirectories in This Archive</H2>

<DL>
<DT><A HREF=".."><B>Up to the Parent Directory</B><P></a>
<DT><a href="Charles_Platt/"><B>Charles_Platt/</B></A>
<DD>Charles Platt's Anarchy Online. 
<DT><a href="Hakim_Bey/"><B>Hakim_Bey/</B></A>
<DD>This directory holds some publications of Hakim Bey,
    a fixture of the grassroots small press community, who focuses on activism,
    anti-authoritarian resistance, and the creation of &quot;temporary autonomous
    zones&quot;, a variety of virtual or association-based community that net.surfers
    may find rather familiar.
<DT><a href="Henry_David_Thoreau/"><B>Henry_David_Thoreau/</B></A>
<DD>On the Duty of Civil Disobedience, Henry David Thoreau
    [1849, original title: Resistance to Civil Goverment]
<DT><a href="William_S_Burroughs/"><B>William_S_Burroughs/</B></A>
<DD>This archive is material by and about
    William S. Burroughs. It's small, but will grow with time. If you
    have any material by or about William S. Burroughs that you feel
    belongs here, please contact us via email (mech@eff.org) and
    (flesh@wps.com). Special thanks to Chris Klausmeier 
    &lt;cklausme@jarthur.cs.hmc.edu&gt; for his contributions, and suport.
</DL>

