<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>What's New at the Cuindlis Genealogy Site?</TITLE></HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ee"
vlink="03066a" alink="ff0000">
<I>See also the <A HREF="comingsoon.html">Coming Soon</A> and <A
HREF="fixes.html">Fixes</A> pages</I>
<H2>What's New at the Cuindlis Genealogy Site?</H2>
<I>Last update: June 3, 1996</I>
<HR>
<H3>* <A HREF="GenWeb/genweb.html">The GenWeb & GEDCOM Genealogy 
Databases</A></H3> 
<UL>
<LI>New database! Now almost 4000 individuals!  Added a load of 
McCandlesses and their Critchlow and Lawrence and Davidson, et al., 
relatives (mostly Butler Co., PA). Also quite a few modern-day folks, 
plus some short but interesting lines, including that of David Colbert 
McCanles/McCandless (gunned down by "Wild Bill" Hickock) and his 
descenant Bruce McCandless III - first Cuindlis-descendant in space!
(June 3 1996)
<LI>There are also new <A HREF="fixes.html">fixes</A> for various problems.
(June 3 1996)
<LI>IGM (see below) turned out not to work right. Seems to not export any 
info other than name, and the search engine didnt' work. Oh well.
(June 3 1996)

<LI>Re-generated database and indexes (to fix misindexing in GENDEX.txt
file, which is used by Gene Stark's GenDex server).
Looking into indexing via IGM as well as, or in place of, GED2HTML.
Check back in a few weeks for major database update! Several hundred new 
folks. (June 1, 1996)  <B>Update, as of Dec. 1996</B>: The above-mentioned 
additions did not occur, as something has gone wrong with my genealogy 
software, a severe bug I have yet to track down. Working on it. Please check
back sometime in the first quarter of 1997.)

<LI>Updated database, with quite a few new folks (total is 
over
2700 now). See <A HREF="fixes.html">here for list of fixes</A>. (Apr. 23, 
1996)
<LI>Also updated the <A HREF="geocodes.list">country/state/county codes list</A>,
and the new codes are used in the database. (Apr. 18, 1993)
</UL>

<H3>* <A HREF="Tartan/">The Tartan Page</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="Tartan/index.html#IMAGES">New images!</A> Far better quality 
than the previous set. I hand-edited these to remove "noise". (May 10, 1996)
<LI><A HREF="Tartan/index.html#FAQ">Frequently Asked Questions (and 
Answers)</A> now appear at the end of the tartan page. (May 8, 1996)
</UL>

<H3>* Misc</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Added a few more folks to the <A HREF="online.html">Cuindlises on the 
Net</A> Page
(June 3, 1996)
<LI>Added some minor notes & clarifications to the <A HREF="variants.html">
Cuindlis name variants</A> page. (Dec. 25, 1996 - Happy Holidays!)
</UL>
