<H3>Assimilated, Merged, Converged and Possibly Related Names</H3>
It is possible that some few people of Cuindlis descent have borne or 
still bear any of the following similar but in many cases differently-derived names.
In such cases, the majority of people with this name may not be related to 
Cuindlis if any of them are. Such names would have been arrived at by 
Cuindlises through various means, that would range from ignorant 
immigration officials mangling the spelling, through assimilation of a 
similar but more common local name that everone knows, to a shift in 
pronunciation and spelling to avoid political troubles.<P>

Some of these names probably *are* derived directly from Cuindlis, but 
*also* derived from other sources. These are examples of merging or 
convergence. Candles is a good example - it obviously derives from 
Cuindlis -> Candless - > Candles, but also equally obviously derives from 
C[h]andle[r] -> Candle -> Candles, if not a candle-maker 
occupationally-derived name in it's own right (e.g. rather than a 
derivative of one like Chandler or Candler).  NOT listed here at all are
names from which people have "migrated" to Cuindlis variants. I know of
one case of a McAndrews who changed his name to McCandless (he was in the 
McCandless-dominated Butler, PA area, and such a name change could have 
made good economic or political sense. Such cases are rather rare and
don't represent patterns, just curiosities.<P>

There are also names in this section for which the present author has 
no idea of derivation, but which might, or might very well not, be 
related in any way, but seem to be "likely suspects". And lastly there are 
few (e.g. Quinlak) that look suspiciously like typos for more common 
spellings, but which could represent genuine variants, or even entirely 
unrelated names.<P>

<H5>(**) = The vast majority of people by this name are not related to the 
Cuindlis lines, but are descended from candlemakers (chandlers).<P>

(***) = The vast majority of people by this name are Hispanic, and no 
relation at all to the Cuindlis families.<P>

(****) = The vast majority of people by this name are Filipino, and no 
relation at all to the Cuindlis families.<P></H5>




