<DT><B><A HREF="http://vmag.law.vill.edu">Villanova Law School Center for 
Information Law &amp; Policy</A></B>
<DD>Provides links to virtual arbitration experiment, government info 
locators, & other legal resources.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.cli.org/">Cyberspace Law Institute</A></B>
<DD> studies, and helps to develop, the new
   forms of law and law-making required by the growth of global
   communications networks and online communities.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.cli.org/sysopl/sysopl.html">A Short Course
on Sysop Liability</A></B>
<DD>by the Cyberspace Law Institute
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.counsel.com/cyberspace/">A virtual "Course on 
Cyberspace Law for Non-Lawyers"</A></B>
<DD>by Profs. Larry Lessig, David Post, and Eugene Volokh.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.e-legal.com/">Electronic Legal Source</A></B>
<DD>This library is stocked with free legal forms and information
for both the general public and legal practitioners. You'll find
legal news, dictionaries, research links and directories of law
firms/schools. A small portion of the MANY free forms online include:
Proof of Service by Mail; Answer to Worker's Compensation Petition;
Loan Agreement; General Contractor's Agreement, and our personal
favorite, a Web Site Design, Storage, and Promotion Agreement.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.barcouncil.com">LIBS</A></B>
<DD>"The Latest Information for Barristers & Solicitors" - project which 
aims to be an extensive and in-depth site
covering all aspects of United Kingdom and Commonwealth law.  There is 
also a wide International section.
</DL>

