<HEAD>
<TITLE> Computers and Academic Freedom News</TITLE>
<BODY>
<h1>
<IMG SRC="/CAF/caf.gif"></A> <b>Computers and Academic Freedom News</b></h1> <p>

<h2>Abstract</h2>
<ol>
<pre>
[Week ending jan 02 1994

========================== KEY ================================
The words after the numbers are a short PARAPHRASES of the
articles, or QUOTES from them, NOT AN OBJECTIVE SUMMARY and
not necessarily my opinion.
===============================================================

</pre>
<li> <A HREF="#1993Dec27.100502.13411@clarinet.com">
Where pirate groups could lead us...</a>
<pre>
    [Paraphrase: The most likely way for Playboy, etc. to assert their
    copyright would be to send lawyer letters to key sites. No one would go
    to jail under this scenario, and it's possible that few (if any) would
    get sued. However, the reputation of USENET in the wider world would
    be hurt badly. Also some sites would cut newsgroups more widely than
    necessary.]
</pre>
