<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="960924_cap_house_docs_online.letter"><B>960924_cap_house_docs_online.letter</B></a>
<DD>Letter to the US House of
    Representatives from Congressional Accountability Project, EFF, and
    many other groups (+ over 700 citizens) demanding online access to
    vital Congressional documents. Even the Dept. of Justice civil librarian
    signed on. Introductory message is followed by the letter, which goes
    into considerable detail about which documents are needed, and why.
    If you've ever wondered what lobbyists get to see that you don't, read
    this!
<DT><a href="campaign_finance_reform.alert"><B>campaign_finance_reform.alert</B></a>
<DD>May 1994 update on the Campaign Finance
    Reform Initiative
<DT><a href="campaign_finance_reform_1.alert"><B>campaign_finance_reform_1.alert</B></a>
<DD>June 1994 update explaining that the
    &quot;Prospects for winning a campaign finance reform bill this year are
    fading in the face of House leadership's unwillingness to craft a workable 
    campaign finance reform bill.&quot;
<DT><a href="campaign_finance_reform_1.alert"><B>campaign_finance_reform_1.alert</B></a>
<DD>August 1994 update noting that
    Campaign finance reform looks bleak.
<DT><a href="campaign_finance_reform_2.alert"><B>campaign_finance_reform_2.alert</B></a>
<DD>Campaign finance reform is in serious trouble
    entangled in conference comittee from which it may never emerge. 
<DT><a href="citizen_access_to_govt_info.article"><B>citizen_access_to_govt_info.article</B></a>
<DD>July 1994 Congressional Reform Briefing
    discussing the lack of citizen access to basic government information 
    like the full text of bills, the Congressional Record, the
    Federal Register, etc. Includes a letter to Michael DiMario proposing
    changes to allow greater citizen access.
<DT><a href="cong_gift_reform.alert"><B>cong_gift_reform.alert</B></a>
<DD>April 1994 Congressional Reform Briefing
    discussing congressional gift reform including relevant arguments,
    history, and contact information
<DT><a href="cong_gift_reform_1.alert"><B>cong_gift_reform_1.alert</B></a>
<DD>April 1994 Congressional Gift Reform
    Alert announcing Senator Levin's gift reform bill and discussing its
    weaknesses. Also discusses the issue of gift reform in general.
<DT><a href="cong_pay.brief"><B>cong_pay.brief</B></a>
<DD>July 1994 Congressional Reform Briefings
    including a letter to the editor written by former U.S. Senator William
    Proxmire (D-WI) discussing the gross overpayment of the staff
    and members of Congress
<DT><a href="cong_gift_reform.update"><B>cong_gift_reform.update</B></a>
<DD>may 1994 Congressional Gift Reform Update
    announcing that the gift reform bills of HOR and Senate will be being
    meashed but that support for a compromise bill is lacking.
<DT><a href="cong_pensions.article"><B>cong_pensions.article</B></a>
<DD>august 1994 Congressional Reform Briefings
    discussing the pension system for members of congress.
<DT><a href="cong_reform.platform"><B>cong_reform.platform</B></a>
<DD>September 1994 Congressional Reform
    Report outlining the Congressional Accountability Project's Congressional
    Reform Platform for 1994
<DT><a href="cong_reform_nadar.brief"><B>cong_reform_nadar.brief</B></a>
<DD>September 1994 Congressional Reform
    Briefing &quot;Give Congress an &quot;F&quot; for their Failure to Pass Congressional
    Reform&quot; By Ralph Nader and Gary Ruskin
<DT><a href="cut_cong_pay.article"><B>cut_cong_pay.article</B></a>
<DD>May 1994 Congressional Reform Briefings explaining
    why members of congress should cut congressional pay levels.
<DT><a href="free_fed_online_access.brief"><B>free_fed_online_access.brief</B></a>
<DD>October 1994 Congressional Reform
    Briefings describing TAP and CAP programs for increasing citizens access
    to government information.
<DT><a href="gift_reform_uwsa.opinion"><B>gift_reform_uwsa.opinion</B></a>
<DD>October 1994 Congressional Reform Briefings
    discussing UNITED WE STAND AMERICA, Inc.'s Position on Gift Reform
<DT><a href="hor_info.announce"><B>hor_info.announce</B></a>
<DD>July 1994 announcement that the HOR has
    released the text of House bills on the WAIS server which is a
    &quot;victory for citizen access to basic federal government information.&quot;
<DT><a href="lobby_disclosure_act.faq"><B>lobby_disclosure_act.faq</B></a>
<DD>October 1994 Congressional Reform
    Briefings discussing Myths and Facts on the Lobbying Disclosure Act
    of 1994.
<DT><a href="none_of_the_above.article"><B>none_of_the_above.article</B></a>
<DD>October 1994 Congressional Reform Briefings by 
    Ralph Nader expressing the need for A None of the Above (NOTA) line on the
    ballot.
<DT><a href="personal_use_of_campaign_funds.article"><B>personal_use_of_campaign_funds.article</B></a>
<DD>September 1994 Congressional Reform
    Briefings discussing the personal use of campaign funds.
<DT><a href="warchests.article"><B>warchests.article</B></a>
<DD>June 1994 Congressional Reform Briefings
    discussing the spending of Campaign Warchests to Reduce Federal Deficit
</DL>

