<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="india_dot_vas.guidelines"><B>india_dot_vas.guidelines</B></a>
<DD>The Department of Telecommunications
    March 1994 &quot;Value Added Services Licensing Information&quot;
<DT><a href="india_natl_telecom_0594.policy"><B>india_natl_telecom_0594.policy</B></a>
<DD>The National Telecommunications Policy of
    1994 which &quot;aims at improving India's competitiveness in the global
    market and rapid growth of exports. Another element of the new
    economic policy is attracting foreign direct investment and 
    stimulating domestic investment. Telecommunication services of
    world class quality are necessary for the success of this policy.
    It is, therefore, necessary to give the highest priority to the 
    development of telecom services in the country.&quot;
<DT><a href="india_online.article"><B>india_online.article</B></a>
<DD>&quot;WIRING INTO THE WORLD&quot;, by Arun Katiyar
    India has begun to tap the bewildering potential of computer networks
    and, with an increasing number of people going online, the country is
    poised to join an international community of info surfers.
</DL>

