<HEAD>
<TITLE>Selena Sol's Fringe Culture Hotlist</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = "FFFFFF" TEXT = "000000">

<H3>Test the Bleeding Edge</H3>
(Fringe culture, weird science, underground scene, cyberian diversions)

<P>
<IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Icons/Lines/line_barbwire.gif" 
ALT = "_____________________________________________________________________">
<P>

<H3>Alternative Culture</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF = "http://www.vivid.com">Vivid</A>
<LI><A HREF = "http://kzsu.stanford.edu/cgi-bin/uwi/reviews.pl?3+0">Hot 
    and Cool pointers...pretty extensive and cool</a>
<LI>EFF <A HREF = "http://www.eff.org/pub/Net_culture/">Net Culture</A> 
    Archive
<LI><A HREF = "http://www.ocf.berkeley.edu/~lizi/hyper-weird/0.1.html"> 
    Hyper-Weirdness</A> WWW Archive (Inspired by "High Weirdness by Email", 
    in turn inspired by the SubGenius "High Weirdness by Mail" book) 
<LI>Internet Wiretap's <A HREF = "gopher://wiretap.Spies.COM:70/11/Library/Fringe/">Fringe</A> 
    Gopher - conspiracies, the gross & disgusting, the paranormal, the 
    Pharmacological Cornucopia, UFOs and more!
<LI><A HREF = "http://venus.mcs.com/~flowers/html/cybernet.html">CyberSight</A> 
    "the central on-line 'jumping off' point for alternative information 
    seekers" 
<LI><A HREF = "http://fringeware.com">FringeWare</A> WWW Server
<LI><A HREF = "http://bazaar.com/underground.html">Underground Net</A> Server
<LI><A HREF = "http://hyperreal.com">Hyperreal</A>, source of info on 
    raves, ambient music, e-pubs, a "MASSIVE" music archive, shareware, net 
    info, and the alt.drugs archives
<LI><A HREF = "http://kzsu.stanford.edu/uwi.html">The Web's Edge</A>, 
    "Underworld Industries' Cultural Playground"
<LI>Internet Town Hall/Internet Talk Radio Travelling Circus & 
    <A HREF = "http://town.hall.org/circus/circus.html">Cyberstation</A>
<LI>A-Albionic's <A HREF="gopher://garnet.msen.com:70/11/vendor/a-albionic">New 
    Paradigms Project</A> Gopher Server
<LI>The Foundation for Neo-cognitive & Ontological Research & Development 
    (<A HREF = "http://io.com/user/blade/fnord.html">FNORD</A>)'s Discordian 
    Site 
<LI>The <A HREF = "http://www.resort.com/~banshee/Faire/index.html">Renaissance 
    Faire</A> WWW Archive - list of ren-fests, info on the 
    re-enactment subculture, folksong sound files, SCA, etc.
<LI>The <A HREF = "http://web.kaleida.com/u/danfuzz/info/words/wall_o_shame/">Wall-o-Shame</A>, 
    an "attempt to characterize the erosion of our world"
<LI><A HREF = "http://www.ramp.com:80/~trisha/main.html/">Brandy's</A>, the 
    first cyberspatial brothel. Uh, yeah.
<LI><A HREF="http://web.cps.msu.edu/~dunhamda/dw/dansworld.html">Dan's 
    World</A> Skatepunk Corner
<LI><A HREF="http://www.vampyre.wis.net/vampyre/index.html">Vampyres 
    Only</A> 
<LI><A HREF="http://gertrude.art.uiuc.edu/ludgate/the/place.html">The 
    Place</A> [Note: works best for Mac users]
<LI>ChibaMOO: The <A HREF="http://sensemedia.net/sprawl/">Sprawl</A> - a 
    cyberpunkish WWW MOO experience!
<LI>Bob's List of <A HREF="http://www.dcs.qmw.ac.uk/~bob/stuff/gpickup.html">Gothic Pick-Up 
    Lines</A>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.gold.net/lynx/fringe/index.html">FringeWeb</A> Server
<LI>[see also <A HREF="#ARTS"> Arts & Leisure</A> Section - alternative 
    tunes, performance and art!]
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cybercafe.org/cybercafe/">CyberCafe</A>
<LI>CyberCafe's list of <A HREF="http://www.cybercafe.org/cybercafe/pubtel/pubtel.html">public 
    telephones and their numbers</A> - the idea is to use them as a means of 
    guerrilla networking - not everyone has their own phone.
<LI>Genuine gossip and firsthand accounts of daily 
    <A HREF="http://www.lib.umich.edu/pap/HomePage.html">life in ancient 
    Egypt</A> (in translation of course).  Take a break from the tabloid 
    mess of the 1990s!
</UL>

<H3>Fringe Politics</H3>
<UL>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://saturn.uaamath.alaska.edu/~kane/oceania_start.html"> 
    Oceania</A> Project WWW Server (a.k.a. Atlantis Project; to form a new, 
    floating, man-made country)
<LI>J. Will Pierce's <A HREF="http://www.rpi.edu/~pier1/phil/objectivism.html"> Objectivism</A> 
    WWW Archive
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.contrib.andrew.cmu.edu/usr/tp0x/chomsky.html">Noam 
    Chomsky</A> WWW Archive
</UL>

<H3>Weird Science</H3>(and maybe a little pseudo-science for good measure)<BR>
<UL>
<LI>SEEKER1's <A HREF="http://www.clas.ufl.edu/anthro/Seeker1_s_CyberAnthro_Page.html">CyberAnthropology</A> Pages
<LI>David Chaum's <A HREF="http://digicash.support.nl"> DigiCash</A> 
    Digital Money System WWW Server
<LI><A HREF="http://www.uio.no/~mwatz/memetics/">Memetics</A> WWW Archive
<LI>EINet Galaxy <A HREF="http://galaxy.einet.net/galaxy/Engineering-and-Technology/Biomedical-Engineering/Cryonics.html">Cryonics</A> WWW Archive
<LI>EINet Galaxy <A HREF="http://galaxy.einet.net/galaxy/Engineering-and-Technology/Biomedical-Engineering/Cryonics.html">Genetic Engineering</A> WWW Archive
<LI>Jack Sarfatti's <A HREF="http://128.194.15.32/~dml601a/ssd/sdhp.html">Star Ship Design 
    Academy</A> - FTL, Relativity paradoxes, space bases & more!
<LI>UMD SSL project's <A HREF="http://ssl.umd.edu/">Human & Robotic 
    Performance in Space</A> Web Pages
<LI>CWRU's <A HREF="gopher://neurogopher.neur.cwru.edu">NeuroGopher</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cnam.fr/fractals.html">Fractal</A> Pictures & 
    Animations WWW Server
<LI>Apple's <A HREF="ftp://bric-a-brac.apple.com/pub/VR/">Virtual 
    Reality</A> FTP Archive
<LI>International <A HREF="gopher://usa.net:70/11/News%20and%20Information/tesla">Tesla</A> 
    Society Gopher Archive
<LI>Info on <A HREF="http://town.hall.org/trendy/trendy.html">New 
    Internet Protocols</A> (IPng, SIPP, TUBA, etc.)
<LI>Labyrinth and <A HREF="http://vrml.wired.com/">VRML</A>, the new 
    Virtual Reality Modeling Language - beyond the World Wide Web!
<LI>Info on the Knowledge Query & Manipulation Language 
    (<A HREF="http://www.cs.umbc.edu/kqml/">KQML</A>) for software agent 
    communications
<LI>Toby's <A HREF="http://www.mcs.net/~utobia/WWW_pages/NetscapePrototype.html"Netscape Fantasy Prototype GUI</A> for WWW exploration (requires Mac Photoshop 3.0; non-animated demo viewable with any GIF graphics viewer)
<LI>Pages on <A HREF="http://synap.neuro.sfc.keio.ac.jp/~aly/polygon/polygon.html">3D 
    modelling</A> for WWW
<LI>U.S. Army page on <A HREF="http://info.arl.army.mil/ACIS/ACD/SciVis/sci.rlpg.html">Regenerative Liquid Propellant Guns</A>, whatever those are.
<LI>Journal of Artificial Intelligence Research 
    (<A HREF="http://www.cs.washington.edu/research/jair/home.html">JAIR</A>)
<LI><A HREF="http://microship.ucsd.edu/">Nomadic Research Labs</A> - 
    Behemoth/Winnebiko, the bicycle to end all bicyles (even has a satellite 
    net.link!), the Sea Moss MicroShip, and more technomadness
<LI>More <A HREF="http://www.fred.net/kathy/technomads.html">Technomads</A> pages
<LI><A HREF="http://www1.cern.ch/NeuralNets/nnwInHep.html">Neural 
    Networks in High Energy Physics</A> at the Royal Institute of 
    Technology, Stockholm, Sweden. 
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.butterfly.net/astro/">Real Astrology</A> Server
<LI>Search for Extra-Terrestria Intelligence 
    (<A HREF="http://www.metrolink.com/seti/SETI.html">SETI</A>) Institute 
    WWW Server 
</UL>

<A NAME="ARTS"></A>
<H3>Arts & Leisure</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF = "http://www.facade.com/">Facade</A> - an excellent site for 
    Tarot Card readings and biorythms...
<LI><A HREF="gopher://srl.org:70/11ftp%3asrl%3apub%3a">Survival Research 
    Laboratories</A> Gopher/FTP archive - pictures, schedules & info on the 
    first robotic performance art troupe
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ifi.uio.no/~terjesa/front242/main.html">Front 
    242</A> WWW Archive
<LI>Home pages of the band <A HREF="http://164.92.5.51/ed.html"Electrode 
    Dingus 2026</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nitv.net/~mech/F5/f5index.html">Factsheet 5</A> - 
    the world-wide index of zines, e-publications, and mail-art
<LI>CyberDen Alternative Music & Entertainment <A HREF="ftp://cyberden.com">FTP</A> Server
<LI>CyberDen <A HREF="telnet://cyberden.com">BBS</A> (telnet)
<LI>Internet <A HREF="http://www.iuma.com/index.html">Underground Music 
    WWW</A> Archive
<LI>Internet <A HREF="gopher://calypso-2.oit.unc.edu.:70/11/sunsite.d/iuma.d">Underground 
    Music Gopher</A> Archive (maybe a separate project?)
<LI><A HREF="http://web.cps.msu.edu/~cookeri1/charnel.catalog.html">Charnel</A> 
    Records WWW Page
<LI><A HREF="http://www.wimsey.com/nettwerk/">Nettwerk</A> Records WWW Page
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ugcs.caltech.edu/~werdna/grotesque/grotesque.html">Horror, Fantasy & the Grotesque in Art</A> Archive
<LI>Baltimore's <A HREF="http://www.clark.net/pub/atomicbk/home.html">Atomic Books</A>: 
    "weirdest bookstore on the net" 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.wired.com/"> WIRED Magazine WWW</A> Server
<LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.wired.com"> WIRED Magazine Gopher</A> Server
<LI>WIRED's <A HREF="http://www.hotwired.com/">HotWired</A> WWW BBS
<LI><A HREF="http://artaids.dcs.qmw.ac.uk:8001/">ArtAIDS</A> 
    Collaborative Online Art Gallery (may require NetScape or emacs)
<LI>The <A HREF="http://gertrude.art.uiuc.edu/@art/gallery.html">@art 
    gallery</A>
<LI><A HREF="gopher://artliason.dorsai.org/">Artliason</A> Virtual Gallery
<LI><A HREF="http://sunsite.unc.edu/otis/otis.html">OTIS</A> 
    Collaborative Art Project WWW Gallery
<LI>International Interactive <A HREF="http://porsche.boltz.cs.cmu.edu:8001/htbin/mjwgenform"> Genetic 
    Art</A> WWW Gallery
<LI>Gallery of <A HREF="http://bazaar.com/Art/mendoza.html">Putrid 
    Afterthought</A> and the Church of Cybernetic Rot
<LI><A HREF="http://gertrude.art.uiuc.edu/~Dialect/common.html">Dialect</A>, "an 
    artist's collective interested in how to use new electronic and 
    communications technologies to reach new audiences."
<LI>Big Pile of Links to <A HREF="http://sunsite.unc.edu/otis/art-links.html"> Virtual Art 
    Galleries</A> All Over the Net
<LI>New World Headquarters (<A HREF=http://www.wimsey.com/~jmax/index.html">NWHQ</A>) hypermedia arts 
    journal
<LI>Best-quality Audio Web Poems (<A HREF="http://www.cs.brown.edu/fun/bawp">BAWP</A>)
<LI><A HREF="gopher://fido.wps.com:70/11/william_s_burroughs/">William S. 
    Burroughs</A> Publications Gopher
<LI><A HREF="gopher://fido.wps.com:70/11/hunter_s_thompson/">Hunter S. 
    Thompson</A> Publications & Pictures Gopher
<LI><A HREF="gopher://fido.wps.com:70/11/pigdog/potpourri-a-video-forum/mykel-board">Mykel Board</A> Unground Reviews and other stuff via gopher
</UL>

<H3>Erotica</H3>
<UL>
<A HREF="http://www.ag.com/condom/country">Condom Country</A> - order 
    condoms online, get info on prophylactics and safe sex, etc.
</UL>

<H3>Miscellaneous</H3>

<UL>
<LI>Be Taken to a <I>Random</I> Server Somewhere on the Matrix, With WWW 
    <A HREF="http://kuhttp.cc.ukans.edu/cwis/organizations/kucia/uroulette/uroulette.html"> URouLette</A> - a random URL generator
</UL> 

