<head>

<title>NorthStar Archives</title>

</head>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF text=#053D8B>
<img ALIGN=left src="ns.gif">

</h1></center>

<dl>

<p><b><dt>Who writes the articles?</b>

<dd>Internet Users like you and me rather than corporate media with corporate opinions. I have written several of them myself and in conjunction with independent writers. The editor has breathed life into every piece submitted. The overall effect is an easy to read, concise report of how current political events are or could be effecting the Internet from the Internet users themselves.<p>

Send article submissions for NorthStar to <A href="mailto:proteios@indirect.com">proteios@indirect.com</a>.

<p><b><dt>How do I subscribe?</b>

<dd><A href="mailto:proteios@indirect.com">Click here to subscribe to Northstar</a></b><br>

put "subscribe NorthStar (your email)" in the body of the message<br>

*You will recieve the HTML version. If (for any reason) you would prefer to receive the original ascii version of NorthStar:<br>

put "subscribe NorthStar-ascii (your email)" in the body of the message

<p><b><dt>Why did you start NorthStar?</b>

<dd>In the true spirit of the Internet, we decided to write a newsletter that gives insightful and informed perspectives from Internet Users rather than centralized media sources. It is clear that the Internet Users alone know what the Internet is. If you have ever watched the TV news bastardize even the most basic of computer terms or activities, you know what we are referring to. They are unable to properly report and inform people about the Internet. There 'informing' the public depends on a public that is even less aware of the Internet than they are. Frightening! So

<p><b><dt>What do you hope to accomplish with NorthStar?</b>

<dd>All Internet Users realize that this medium is capable of much more than the government will ever allow it to be used for. To convey to everyone, everywhere that the Internet has the ability to increase our ability to participate in government, be active in it and be aware of what comprises it while simultaneously having the ability to facilitate government survellience and censorship of a magnitude only theorized in a science fiction story written in 1948.</dl>

<p>

<A href="http://www.indirect.com/www/proteios/northstar.html"><img border=0 align="bottom" src="ret.gif">Return to NorthStar Archives Main Page</a>

</body>

