<h1><img src="/pub/Graphics/Icons/eff3d_white_icon.gif" ALT="">
<a name="top">EFF &quot;Legislation &amp; Regulation - Freedom Shrine: Historical Freedom Documents&quot; Archive</a></h1>

<H5>http://www.eff.org/pub/Legislation/Freedom_Shrine/
</H5>



<h6>Last Updated Mon Dec 16 17:31:43 PDT 1996</h6><br>
<TABLE BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER>
<TD><A HREF="#files">Files</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#dirs">Subdirectories</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#onsite">On-Site Links</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#offsite">Off-Site Links</A></TD>
</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="README"><B>README</B></a>
<DD>This directory contains the &quot;Freedom Shrine&quot; a collection of
    freedom-related documents common to many internet sites, especially
    free-nets. This README file has more info on the idea.
<DT><a href="art_11_declaration_excerpt_english.fr"><B>art_11_declaration_excerpt_english.fr</B></a>
<DD>Excerpt from Article 11 of the 
    French Constitution's Declaration of the Rights of the Man &amp; Citizen,
    specifying the nature and limitations of intellectual freedom.
    (somewhat similar to he US First Amendment or the Canadian Charter of 
    Rights and Freedoms section on free speech.) In English.
<DT><a href="art_21_constitution_english.jp"><B>art_21_constitution_english.jp</B></a>
<DD>Article 21 of the Constitution of Japan; 
    guarantees free speech and other rights. In English.
