<DT><a href="960502_aclu_immig_bill.announce"><B>960502_aclu_immig_bill.announce</B></a>
<DD>ACLU Calls Senate Immigration Bill
    &quot;Unconstitutional, Unwise and Un-American&quot;
<DT><a href="960402_aclu_immig_bill_and_abuse.announce"><B>960402_aclu_immig_bill_and_abuse.announce</B></a>
<DD>ACLU Condemns Police Beating 
    of Immigrants; Warns that Immig. Bills Would Open Doors to More Abuses
<DT><a href="960318_aclu_terror_immig_bills.announce"><B>960318_aclu_terror_immig_bills.announce</B></a>
<DD>Press releases from ACLU,
    regarding &quot;Congressional shell game&quot;: Dangerous provisions stripped from
    terrorism bill only to reappear a week later in anti-immigration bill!
<DT><a href="960313_aclu_terror_immig_bills.article"><B>960313_aclu_terror_immig_bills.article</B></a>
<DD>Op-ed piece by ACLU's Laura W.
    Murphy: Congress might as well declare March 13-20 &quot;National Wiretap
    Week&quot;, given the content of the anti-terrorism and anti-immigration bills
    our legislature seems hell-bent on passing despite mounting
    constitutionality concerns.
<DT><a href="930723_aclu_immig_bill.announce"><B>930723_aclu_immig_bill.announce</B></a>
<DD>ACLU announcement: &quot;Clinton Immigration 
    Proposal Dangerous and Misguided; Eliminates Judicial Review and Denies 
    Legal Protections to Refugees&quot; (No privacy or free speech threats were 
    in the legislation at this early stage, but it's interesting to see the 
    &quot;evolution&quot; of this bill over 3 years from scare to utterly nightmarish.)
</DL>

