<h2><A NAME="offsite">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/earth2_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Links to Related Off-Site Resources</h2>
<DL>

<DT><B>The Phil Zimmermann (PGP author) <A
HREF="http://www.netresponse.com/zldf">Legal
 Defense Fund</A> WWW Pages</B>
<DT><A HREF="http://web.mit.edu/pgp/"><B>Phil's Pretty Good Software</B> 
site</A> 
<DD>Home pages for PGP and PGPfone.
<DT><B><A 
HREF="http://www.highware.com/highware/safemail/safemail.htm">Pretty
Safe Mail</A></B>
<DD>Mac (Windows soon) PGP-compatible emailing utility, that allows
encrypted sending of documents from any application, key signing and 
management, and decryption of PGP-encoded files (even if sending user 
does not use Pretty Safe Mail).
 <DT><B>A Great HTMLized <A
HREF="http://www.austinlinks.com/Crypto">PGP
 FAQ</A></B>
<DT><B>Link to <A
href="http://martigny.ai.mit.edu/~bal/pks-toplev.html">PGP
 Key Server</A> WWW Interface at MIT</B>
 <DD>(Requires HTML forms support).
<DT><B>Link to <A HREF="http://www.c2.org/remail/by-www.html">WWW Anonymous
 Remailer Interface</A></B>
 <DD>Requires HTML forms support
<DT><B>Matt Thomlinson's <A
HREF="ftp://ftp.u.washington.edu/public/phantom/cpunk/README.html">Cypherpunk
 Topics</A> WWW Archive</B>
