<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Selena Sol's Public Domain CGI Script Archive and Resource
Library: Help Found</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = "FFFFFF" TEXT = "000000">
<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Scripts/help_found.gif" BORDER = "0"></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE=+2>Help Found</FONT></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<CENTER><P><IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Icons/Lines/smalline.gif"><P></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B><I>Before sending me email, please submit your question to <A HREF =
"http://www.sidestreets.com/info/sssa/">Selena Sol's CGI Scripts
Discussion Forum</A></I></B>
<P>
<DT>Since I opened this page about four months ago, I have been absolutely
smothered in freelance work.  In fact, I'm averaging about 2 shopping
cart installation requests per day.  Obviously, no mortal person could
keep up such a pace with full time work and Grad School.  So recently I
have been coordinating with other CGI programmers who have <B>added in
some way to this page</B> (Don't ask me to be on the list unless you have
contributed to the public domain first)  :) Like me, these programmers
have reasonable rates ($500-$800 for a shopping cart customization for
example), though each of them have their own pricing systems.  Anyway, if you
have freelance work, I would appreciate it if you asked me
first...but...if I am busy, feel free to contact these great people.  
<P>
By the way, the best way to get your questions answered or project 
completed quickly is to make sure that you ask your questions very well.
Please do not simply click and type.  Take some time to think about what 
you want first.  If you are looking for a shopping cart system, for 
example, take some time to consider the fields, or what your order form 
will look like, what type of security you want, what your cliental will 
be like.  Take an hour to define your specs and you may knock off 20% of 
the total cost of development.
<P>

<DL>

<DT><IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Scripts/redarrow.gif" BORDER = "0">
    <A HREF="feedback.html" TARGET = "Resource Window">Selena Sol - 
    Hypermedia Arachnid for Hire</A>
    <DD>Read this <A HREF="../Personal/Resume/commodify.html">faq</A>
    to find out how to commodify Selena Sol

<DT><IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Scripts/redarrow.gif" BORDER = "0">
    <A HREF = "feedback.html" TARGET = "Resource Window">Gunther 
    Birznieks</A>
    <DD>Gunther specializes in Shopping Cart Scripts, especially SQL database
    gateways.  He is a fantastic hacker and great person too.

<DT><IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Scripts/redarrow.gif" BORDER = "0">
    <A HREF="feedback.html" TARGET = "Resource Window">Wojciech Tryc</A>
    <DD>Wojciech is a Systems Architect for a Consulting Firm in Ottawa,
    Canada with experience in Perl, C, Sed, Awk, Shell, PHP, mSQL 
    programming and HTML/CGI of course.

<DT><IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Scripts/redarrow.gif" BORDER = "0">
    <A HREF="feedback.html" TARGET = "Resource Window">Nicolaus G. Bauman</A>
    <DD>Nicolaus hacked through the Digicon scripts long enough to
    significantly improve them.  He would be a fine choice as well!

<DT><IMG SRC = "../Graphics/Scripts/redarrow.gif" BORDER = "0">
    <A HREF = "http://www.microlink.net/~gentle/Demo" TARGET = 
    "Resource Window">Rod 
    Gentle</A>
    <DD>Rod has customized most of my scripts for his site and
